solomon.def: (old testament) son of david and king of israel noted for his wisdom (10th century bc)

buddhism.def: a religion represented by the many groups (especially in asia) that profess various forms of the buddhist doctrine and that venerate buddha

chalcedony.def: a milky or greyish translucent to transparent quartz

iranian.def: a native or inhabitant of iran

mentor.def: a wise and trusted guide and advisor

wisdom.def: accumulated knowledge or erudition or enlightenment

profess.def: practice as a profession, teach, or claim to be knowledgeable about

assemble.def: create by putting components or members together

enlightenment.def: education that results in understanding and the spread of knowledge

knowledgeable.def: highly educated; having extensive information or understanding

scholars.def: a learned person (especially in the humanities); someone who by long study has gained mastery in one or more disciplines

scholarship.def: financial aid provided to a student on the basis of academic merit

mastery.def: great skillfulness and knowledge of some subject or activity

academic.def: an educator who works at a college or university

skillfulness.def: the state of being cognitively skillful
